Project Outcomes 



HACU’s National Internship Program’s (HNIP) motto, Opening Doors of Opportunity, (Abriendo Puertas de Oportunidad) is supported by the following objectives:

1.           Provide students with professional experience that will enable them to make more educated career choices;

2.            Expose students to research, development, technology, and administrative career opportunities in the public and private sector;

3.            Supplement academic student with practical applications for students majoring in related fields and disciplines;

4.            Extend and strengthen the relationship between government agencies/bureaus, HSIs, and other institutions with significant Hispanic enrollment;

5.            Encourage students to explore and possibly pursue careers in the federal government; and

6.            Expose interns to information about corporations and federal government’s outreach efforts that assist, train, and prepare Hispanic students to enter the workforce.



The National Science Foundation utilizes HACU/HNIP to recruit college students for their Summer Scholars Internship Program. In addition to the intern experience at NSF, students also benefit from leadership training and additional logistical support from HNIP. These professional developments are meant to position the interns for success when entering a career with the federal government. The HNIP staff also provide a virtual orientation and acts as human resources to the intern. During the duration of the award, NSF hosted 25 HACU interns in their Summer Scholars Internship Program.

